{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"✓\n    Direction B\n    The Driver Fingerprint\n    \"Every driver has a signature. This is where you find it.\"\n    Forget single-session comparisons. The app builds a full performance identity for every driver — a radar of their strengths across dimensions: qualifying vs. race pace, wet vs. dry, early-stint vs. late-stint tire management, home circuits vs. away. Then you compare fingerprints. \"Who is this driver, and who races like them?\"\n    \n      Radar/spider chart per driver\n      Wet vs. dry split\n      Qualifying vs. race pace delta\n      Tire deg profile\n      \"Similar drivers\" engine\n      Career arc timeline\n    \n    \n      ◆ DRIVER DNA · EARL BAMBER vs. NICK TANDY\n                      Qualifying pace\n          Wet pace ●────────────────● Race pace\n                     /     ██████   \\\n          Tire mgmt ●    ████████    ● Stint length\n                     \\              /\n                       Traffic pace\n      Bamber: qualifying specialist. Tandy: race-day performer.","choice":"fingerprint","id":null,"timestamp":1778381080758}
{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"✓\n    Direction A\n    The Race Debrief\n    \"Stop looking at charts. Start reading the race.\"\n    The app becomes a race analyst. You pick a session and it generates a narrative — automatically identifying the key moments, the pace leaders, the hidden battles. Charts serve the story, not the other way around. It's like a post-race engineer debrief, except the data does the talking.\n    \n      Auto-generated race narrative\n      Key moment detection\n      Stint-by-stint pace story\n      Battle tracker (cars within 2s)\n      Shareable race reports\n    \n    \n      ◆ DAYTONA 2024 · GTP RACE DEBRIEF\n      Lap 1–12 · Dominant opening\n      Bamber exits T1 clean, builds 4.2s gap by lap 8. Class median: 1:43.2. His pace: 1:42.1.\n      Lap 23 · The undercut window\n      Porsche #7 pits 3 laps earlier. Emerges P3, on cold tires. Van der Zande responds lap 26.\n      Lap 41–47 · FCY bunches the field\n      5-car train within 1.8s. Restarts shuffle the top 4...","choice":"story","id":null,"timestamp":1778381081955}
