{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"✓\n    Direction C\n    The Circuit Book\n    \"Every track has a personality. Some drivers get it. Most don't.\"\n    Flip the mental model entirely. Start with a circuit, not a driver. The app becomes a living encyclopedia of every track — who dominates here and why, how conditions affect lap times, the all-time lap record progression, which manufacturers suit the circuit's character. Watkins Glen rewards different skills than Daytona. This is where you prove it.\n    \n      Circuit homepage\n      All-time lap record timeline\n      Track specialists ranking\n      Manufacturer affinity chart\n      Weather impact analysis\n      Circuit vs. circuit comparison\n    \n    \n      ◆ WATKINS GLEN · CIRCUIT PROFILE\n      GTP Track Record  1:40.847  Bamber · 2024 · Dry · 74°F\n      ─────────────────────────────────────\n      Track specialists (2020–2024)\n      #1 Bamber  avg -0.8% vs field\n      #2 Tandy   avg -0.6% vs field\n      #3 Vanthoor avg -0.5% vs field\n      Manufacturer affinity  Porsche dominates high-speed, BMW struggles S2","choice":"circuit","id":null,"timestamp":1778381085455}
